  </p>
  <p><strong>MEMBERS HEALTH CHECK</strong><br>
    Glen and Tracy will be phoning each Incedo member sometime during the next few weeks. We would like to catch up with you all, not just to touch base, but also to go a little deeper. We&rsquo;d love to hear your thoughts from the last MLT update around the WHY Incedo question. We&rsquo;re keen to hear how things really are, your hopes and dreams for the future. As well as how Incedo can serve you and how you can serve Incedo. We&rsquo;re looking forward to chatting with you all and are really keen for some honest reflections and thoughts from you.<br>
  </p>
  <p><strong>SPENDING OVER $1,000</strong><br>
    Please remember to touch base with the MLT if you are spending over $1,000 on any item. And a reminder: don&rsquo;t spend money you do not have or are not certain you will get. This includes signing agreements to purchase or hire without being certain you can fund them. As a nation-wide mission, we are all accountable to each other ... what you do, has an effect on all of us.<br>
  </p>
  <p><strong>SEATTLE/PORTLAND EXCURSION</strong><br>
    A small group of Incedo members were privileged to spend seven days in Seattle and Portland at the end of April, beginning of May. There were two conferences that were attended, Q IDEAS<a href="http://www.qideas.org/event/presentations.aspx"> www.qideas.org/event/presentations.aspx</a> and INHABIT <a href="http://www.inhabitconference.com">www.inhabitconference.com</a> We also spent time with Richard Twiss <a href="http://www.wiconi.com">www.wiconi.com</a> a Native American Indian who&rsquo;s challenged by his Faith, Culture and place in Christianity. Please contact Glen, Mal, Tracy, Gus or Laura if you&rsquo;d like to know more about our time away. Some of out learning&rsquo;s and ideas will be used and shared at this year&rsquo;s Gathering.<br>
  </p>
  <p><strong>WEEKLY PRAYER CONNECTION</strong><br>
    We would like to begin a weekly prayer inter-active connection for Incedo members. </p>
  <p>For this to happen, we need to know how many of us currently have access to SKYPE? Please let the MLT know if you do/don&rsquo;t have access. The prayer connection would run twice a week, 
    once in the morning (maybe Tuesday) and once in the evening, (maybe Thursday). 
    This would be an voluntary opportunity for members to be more effectively connected 
    regularly for prayer and reflection. We would like to begin this in the next two 
    weeks, so please get back to us asap.<br>
  </p>
